#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.39:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga "
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Paṭhamapajjunnadhītusutta → pajjunnadhītusuttaṃ (bj) | pajjunnadhītusuttaṃ (1) (s1) | pajjunnadhītā (1) (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Paṭhamapajjunnadhītusutta "
msgstr "39. With Pajjunna’s Daughter (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn1.39:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn1.39:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.39:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ mahāvanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the beautiful Kokanadā, Pajjunna’s daughter, lighting up the entire Great Wood, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "

msgctxt "sn1.39:1.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.30, pts2ed1.62, sc2
msgctxt "sn1.39:2.1"
msgid "“Vesāliyaṃ vane viharantaṃ, "
msgstr "“Staying in the woods of Vesālī "

# NOTE: See BB on sattassa.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:2.2"
msgid "Aggaṃ sattassa sambuddhaṃ; "
msgstr "is the Buddha, best of beings. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:2.3"
msgid "Kokanadāhamasmi abhivande, "
msgstr "Kokanadā am I who worships him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:2.4"
msgid "Kokanadā pajjunnassa dhītā. "
msgstr "Kokanadā, Pajjuna’s daughter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.39:3.1"
msgid "Sutameva pure āsi, "
msgstr "Previously I had only heard "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:3.2"
msgid "Dhammo cakkhumatānubuddho; "
msgstr "the teaching realized by the seer. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:3.3"
msgid "Sāhaṃ dāni sakkhi jānāmi, "
msgstr "But now I know it as a witness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:3.4"
msgid "Munino desayato sugatassa. "
msgstr "while the sage, the Holy One teaches. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn1.39:4.1"
msgid "Ye keci ariyaṃ dhammaṃ, "
msgstr "There are unintelligent people who go about "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:4.2"
msgid "Vigarahantā caranti dummedhā; "
msgstr "denouncing the noble teaching. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:4.3"
msgid "Upenti roruvaṃ ghoraṃ, "
msgstr "They fall into the terrible Hell of Screams "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:4.4"
msgid "Cirarattaṃ dukkhaṃ anubhavanti. "
msgstr "where they suffer long. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.39:5.1"
msgid "Ye ca kho ariye dhamme, "
msgstr "There are those who have found acceptance and peace "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:5.2"
msgid "Khantiyā upasamena upetā; "
msgstr "in the noble teaching. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:5.3"
msgid "Pahāya mānusaṃ dehaṃ, "
msgstr "After giving up this human body, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.39:5.4"
msgid "Devakāyaṃ paripūressantī”ti. "
msgstr "they swell the hosts of gods.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
